WEBVTT

01:53.770 --> 01:56.048
Seriously, what was that dream...

02:05.552 --> 02:07.030
Get enough rest?

02:07.030 --> 02:09.030
Just a reminder, regular shift today.

02:09.030 --> 02:10.596
You got this!

02:10.596 --> 02:12.438
That's right. Work.

02:13.813 --> 02:16.917
That explains the nightmare.

02:30.900 --> 02:34.222
Here's your iced Americano.

02:35.117 --> 02:36.512
So,

02:36.512 --> 02:37.877
are you doing better now?

02:37.877 --> 02:38.943
Better how?

02:38.943 --> 02:41.422
Remember that chaos right outside here?

02:41.422 --> 02:43.943
You passed out cold.

02:43.943 --> 02:45.638
And the pics went viral.

02:45.638 --> 02:48.422
People tagged you "Haemu Fainting Guy."

02:48.422 --> 02:50.723
And it really was an affair, huh?

02:50.723 --> 02:53.292
The lady's husband?
Deputy Manager Son over at Food Division?

02:53.292 --> 02:55.552
Where does that leave things?

02:55.552 --> 02:57.772
Word is you handle that stuff at Audit.

02:57.772 --> 02:59.943
- Da Young.
- Yeah?

02:59.943 --> 03:01.683
Looks like orders are piling up.

03:02.568 --> 03:04.654
I'm sorry!

03:08.616 --> 03:10.857
Hey, Assistant Manager Noh!

03:10.857 --> 03:12.700
The Haemu Fainting Guy?

03:13.705 --> 03:14.987
Look at you, totally fine.

03:14.987 --> 03:17.161
- All better?
- Yeah, all better.

03:17.161 --> 03:19.813
They put you on affair cases, right?
How did that happen?

03:19.813 --> 03:22.943
- I thought you were thriving at Audit.
- Look.

03:22.943 --> 03:24.727
Not "affairs." PM.

03:24.727 --> 03:27.248
Public Morals.

03:27.248 --> 03:29.308
Know what you're talking about.

03:36.269 --> 03:38.480
Assistant Manager Noh.

03:42.442 --> 03:43.776
Yes, Secretary Park.

03:43.776 --> 03:45.422
I heard what happened.

03:45.422 --> 03:47.205
Are you alright?

03:47.205 --> 03:48.813
I'm fine.

03:48.813 --> 03:50.657
That's a relief.

03:57.623 --> 03:59.834
Oh my, Assistant Manager Noh!

03:59.834 --> 04:01.422
Just now showing up?

04:01.422 --> 04:04.352
So happy to see you I could faint.

04:06.888 --> 04:08.683
Ms. Joo.

04:08.683 --> 04:11.335
That's not something to joke about.

04:11.335 --> 04:13.552
Why not? I think I've earned the right.

04:13.552 --> 04:16.378
The fact that you're here in one piece

04:16.378 --> 04:18.478
is only because I held you up

04:18.478 --> 04:22.565
with both of these arms, alright?

04:23.292 --> 04:26.135
Even threw my wrist out and needed acupuncture.

04:26.726 --> 04:28.465
What an absolute honor.

04:28.465 --> 04:30.527
No big deal.

04:31.908 --> 04:35.508
Let me submit that disciplinary report
on Deputy Manager Son immediately.

04:35.508 --> 04:37.727
That's already been handled.

04:37.727 --> 04:39.770
Excuse me?

04:39.770 --> 04:42.135
It's been wrapped up.

04:44.712 --> 04:47.378
Delicious and drinkable. Massigo.

04:47.378 --> 04:50.351
Through Haemu's distinctive
and cutting-edge food tech

04:50.351 --> 04:53.671
achieving real farm-to-table results,
we firmly believe Massigo

04:53.671 --> 04:55.515
is set to become the lead brand

04:55.515 --> 04:58.422
of Haemu Foods, shaping global food trends.

04:58.422 --> 04:59.943
And with that, I'll wrap up.

04:59.943 --> 05:01.700
Thank you.

05:04.982 --> 05:06.901
Thank you.

05:12.657 --> 05:13.866
Thank you.

05:13.866 --> 05:16.119
We'll give it everything.

05:20.420 --> 05:23.668
Okay, but that still doesn't sit right.

05:23.668 --> 05:25.320
Deputy Manager Jung gets exiled to the factory

05:25.320 --> 05:27.012
while Deputy Manager Son keeps his spot?

05:27.012 --> 05:28.638
Not even removed from the project?

05:28.638 --> 05:29.770
[Joo In Ah]

05:29.770 --> 05:32.552
Honestly, between the two,
the married one, Deputy Manager Son,

05:32.552 --> 05:34.262
has more to answer for
than the single Deputy Manager Jung.

05:34.262 --> 05:37.515
By whose standards, exactly?

05:37.515 --> 05:39.267
Son has consistently performed

05:39.267 --> 05:41.943
and he's leading Food Division's
major new brand.

05:41.943 --> 05:43.248
And Deputy Manager Jung?

05:43.248 --> 05:45.162
Outside of whatever Son pulled her into,

05:45.162 --> 05:47.422
her record and standing aren't impressive.

05:47.422 --> 05:49.550
As far as the company's concerned,
Deputy Manager Jung

05:49.550 --> 05:51.696
is the bigger liability here.

05:51.696 --> 05:53.531
Wouldn't you agree?

05:54.282 --> 05:56.618
But ethically...

06:00.332 --> 06:01.900
Ethics?

06:01.900 --> 06:04.073
What are you, a cop? A judge?

06:04.073 --> 06:07.162
Does this company exist
to hand out gold stars and punishments?

06:07.162 --> 06:09.384
All a company has to care about is

06:09.384 --> 06:11.943
what each employee brings to the table.

06:11.943 --> 06:15.700
Around here, that is ethics and morals.

06:24.145 --> 06:25.354
What, did you expect

06:25.354 --> 06:27.815
some kind of feel-good karma ending?

06:27.815 --> 06:31.444
Cheaters humiliated and hiding in shame?
Like that?

06:33.029 --> 06:36.335
You're a lot greener than you seem.

06:36.335 --> 06:38.873
So then why put me on this?

06:40.900 --> 06:42.743
This kind of work.

06:43.335 --> 06:46.092
Not exactly suited for a naive person.

06:51.335 --> 06:52.727
Actually, you're ideal for it.

06:52.727 --> 06:54.987
- What's the actual...
- Don't let it eat at you too much.

06:54.987 --> 06:57.465
The bigger pay cut landed
on Deputy Manager Son.

06:57.465 --> 07:00.465
And his reputation is already in the gutter.

07:00.465 --> 07:03.422
Performance reviews will reflect all of this.

07:03.422 --> 07:06.962
And if divorce proceedings start,
he's facing legal fallout too.

07:07.785 --> 07:08.814
Alright.

07:08.814 --> 07:10.560
A closed case doesn't need more attention,

07:10.560 --> 07:12.378
so let's nail this next one.

07:12.378 --> 07:14.048
I'm sorry?

07:16.987 --> 07:18.465
CompanyLife.com.

07:18.465 --> 07:21.092
Haven't you been checking it?
Comment section is a mess.

07:50.511 --> 07:55.335
[Episode 2: I'm the Best]

07:55.335 --> 07:57.508
Do something about Section F already.

07:57.508 --> 07:59.465
What is Haemu, some kind of hookup zone?

07:59.465 --> 08:01.465
- Too many gross things spotted there.
- Section F?

08:01.465 --> 08:02.943
It's common knowledge.

08:02.943 --> 08:05.117
HQ's underground parking garage.

08:05.117 --> 08:07.900
- No cameras covering it, right?
- What's all this?

08:07.900 --> 08:11.836
- Not a chance I'd park there.
- How's this news to everyone?

08:11.836 --> 08:15.047
Down on B4 of the garage, Section F,

08:15.047 --> 08:17.117
turns out it's where office couples go.

08:17.117 --> 08:19.508
Married, single, doesn't matter.

08:19.508 --> 08:22.683
Zero cameras facing that direction, pitch dark,

08:22.683 --> 08:24.595
hardly any cars parked on the 4th floor.

08:24.595 --> 08:25.943
Can't beat that.

08:25.943 --> 08:28.117
Quite the expert on this, Mr. Cha.

08:28.117 --> 08:31.508
Just picked it up through the rumor mill.

08:31.508 --> 08:33.422
First things first, let's confirm this.

08:33.422 --> 08:35.508
Running an investigation
off rumors isn't an option.

08:35.508 --> 08:36.652
Understood.

08:36.652 --> 08:39.162
How do we confirm that? Through who?

08:39.162 --> 08:42.335
The team's established a HUMINT network.

08:42.335 --> 08:43.378
Did you say HUMINT?

08:43.378 --> 08:45.205
[Intel collected via human sources
like informants or internal contacts]

08:45.205 --> 08:47.335
[Lee Sun Hwa, HQ Janitor]
Where do I even begin?

08:47.335 --> 08:48.813
Happens all the time.

08:48.813 --> 08:52.030
[Oh Seok Hun, Security Guard]
You catch them, but it's so uncomfortable

08:52.030 --> 08:53.683
you just pretend you didn't see anything.

08:53.683 --> 08:55.030
[Kim Da Young, H Cafe staff]
Section F.

08:55.030 --> 08:56.727
Everyone calls it the hot spot.

08:56.727 --> 08:59.465
[Parking Restriction Notice for Maintenance]

08:59.465 --> 09:01.857
Yeah, that area right there.

09:01.857 --> 09:04.552
Does that spot somehow make it more exciting?

09:04.552 --> 09:08.048
Grown adults with decent jobs,
and this is what they do?

09:09.018 --> 09:10.335
Tell me about it.

09:10.335 --> 09:11.541
Should

09:11.541 --> 09:14.073
anything odd come up, a tip would be great.

09:14.073 --> 09:16.030
Sure thing. Take care.

09:16.030 --> 09:17.830
Yes.

09:19.528 --> 09:20.943
So

09:20.943 --> 09:24.352
our HUMINT has confirmed
the information is legit.

09:27.073 --> 09:29.657
HUMINT, my ass.

09:30.595 --> 09:32.596
- Let's just go eat.
- Oh, right.

09:32.596 --> 09:35.336
Today's cafeteria menu is tonkatsu, miso soup,
and braised potatoes.

09:35.336 --> 09:36.465
I'm not eating at the cafeteria.

09:36.465 --> 09:38.900
Let me look up some places nearby then.

09:38.900 --> 09:41.308
- Don't bother.
- But I...

09:45.305 --> 09:47.726
[Tonight...]

09:52.353 --> 09:54.727
Any plans tonight? It's your birthday.

09:54.727 --> 09:56.727
Going out with your boyfriend?

09:56.727 --> 09:58.162
Not really.

09:58.162 --> 10:00.205
You're being so mysterious.

10:00.205 --> 10:04.092
I keep wondering what type of guy
someone like you sees.

10:41.068 --> 10:43.680
The cafeteria keeps getting worse.

10:43.680 --> 10:45.505
I know, right? Tomorrow we eat out.

10:46.292 --> 10:47.987
- Hey.
- Yeah?

10:47.987 --> 10:49.683
Is that your husband right there?

10:49.683 --> 10:50.987
Mr. Kwon?

10:50.987 --> 10:52.378
Yeah, that's him.

10:52.378 --> 10:54.813
Why aren't you going over to say hello?

10:54.813 --> 10:57.291
Are things tense between you?

10:57.291 --> 10:59.422
No fight. We're good.

10:59.422 --> 11:00.552
Ji Yeon,

11:00.552 --> 11:02.900
once you've been married a few years,

11:02.900 --> 11:05.030
even brushing hands feels weird.

11:05.030 --> 11:07.005
You're always so dramatic.

11:09.727 --> 11:11.335
You two are funny though.

11:11.335 --> 11:12.465
Back when you were dating,

11:12.465 --> 11:14.987
you hid it and acted like total strangers.

11:14.987 --> 11:17.335
Now the whole office knows you're married,

11:17.335 --> 11:18.552
and you still keep your distance?

11:18.552 --> 11:20.900
It's about keeping work and home apart.

11:20.900 --> 11:25.178
Right, sure,
as if home is where the magic happens.

11:27.073 --> 11:29.033
Come on.

11:29.033 --> 11:30.552
You two still getting it on?

11:30.552 --> 11:32.422
Come on.

11:32.422 --> 11:34.873
That's for honeymooners. We're just family.

11:35.770 --> 11:38.030
You guys were so all over each other.

11:38.030 --> 11:40.248
How come every married couple
ends up like this?

11:40.248 --> 11:43.178
Keep the heat up forever and you'll melt, dude.

11:51.030 --> 11:54.073
[Assistant Manager Yeon So Yeong]
[New message received]

11:54.073 --> 11:57.092
College reunion tonight. Going to be late.

11:57.686 --> 11:59.439
Got it.

12:13.494 --> 12:14.537
Oh my.

12:14.537 --> 12:16.288
I'm so sorry!

12:16.288 --> 12:17.508
It's okay.

12:17.508 --> 12:19.033
What is wrong with me?

12:19.033 --> 12:20.900
I'm really sorry.

12:20.900 --> 12:24.162
Don't worry about it. These things happen.

12:24.162 --> 12:25.508
Ms. Sun.

12:25.508 --> 12:27.205
On my way, sir.

12:27.205 --> 12:29.308
- Again, sorry.
- It's alright, go.

12:51.532 --> 12:53.993
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

12:57.872 --> 13:00.040
- Refreshing.
- So refreshing.

13:00.040 --> 13:01.542
- Right?
- Jun Seo!

13:01.542 --> 13:02.552
Over here!

13:02.552 --> 13:04.837
- You got even better looking!
- Long time no see!

13:04.837 --> 13:06.683
- You haven't changed at all.
- You really did.

13:06.683 --> 13:08.857
It slipped my mind to mention
Jun Seo was joining.

13:08.857 --> 13:10.718
My bad.

13:10.718 --> 13:12.117
Don't worry about it.

13:12.117 --> 13:14.787
Please, that breakup was a lifetime ago.

13:22.354 --> 13:23.982
Long time no see, So Yeong.

13:25.149 --> 13:27.638
You look exactly the same.

13:27.638 --> 13:29.962
Not a thing's changed.

13:29.962 --> 13:32.422
Stop it. I look way older now. Don't I?

13:32.422 --> 13:33.782
Not at all.

13:33.782 --> 13:34.813
You look beautiful.

13:34.813 --> 13:36.619
Just like before.

13:36.619 --> 13:39.204
- What's going on with you two?
- Excuse me, I was always the cute one.

13:39.204 --> 13:40.248
Oh, come on.

13:40.248 --> 13:42.791
- You two never change.
- You're killing the vibe here.

13:42.791 --> 13:43.834
Here you go.

13:43.834 --> 13:45.587
Pour me one.

13:47.714 --> 13:49.601
Let's get started.

13:54.857 --> 13:56.508
It's time to vote.

13:56.508 --> 13:58.933
[Final Results: The 3rd Survivor Announcement]

13:58.933 --> 14:01.394
How did his rank slip?

14:05.117 --> 14:07.205
That mission bonus is ridiculously high.

14:07.205 --> 14:09.180
Boys to Planet's final global first round vote

14:09.180 --> 14:11.495
[Final Global Round 1 Vote]
is now underway.

14:11.495 --> 14:13.422
For the Boys to Planet Final Global...

14:13.422 --> 14:14.943
Hold on, is double voting allowed?

14:14.943 --> 14:17.683
Head to the Boys to Planet page,

14:17.683 --> 14:20.943
open the voting tab, pick one contestant...

14:20.943 --> 14:22.205
Who is it?

14:22.205 --> 14:24.135
After that...

14:26.585 --> 14:29.923
Hey. Let's grab a drink. It's been a while.

14:41.508 --> 14:42.770
What are you trying to do here?

14:42.770 --> 14:45.292
Are we getting back together?

14:45.292 --> 14:47.508
You want to get back together?

14:47.508 --> 14:49.352
If not, forget it.

14:50.727 --> 14:53.335
You're always, without fail,
completely one-sided.

14:53.335 --> 14:56.248
Out of nowhere you said
"let's date," then vanished.

14:56.248 --> 14:58.595
Two full years later you show up
at my door for what?

14:58.595 --> 15:00.683
- "Have a drink?"
- So?

15:00.683 --> 15:03.162
Did it crush you when I left?

15:03.162 --> 15:05.162
Did you shed any tears for me?

15:05.162 --> 15:06.552
Of course not.

15:06.552 --> 15:07.987
You just let me leave

15:07.987 --> 15:09.595
with that "suit yourself" attitude.

15:09.595 --> 15:12.727
I'm sure you didn't even blink,
let alone cry, Mr. Unbothered.

15:12.727 --> 15:15.265
Drink this. Let it all go.

15:25.928 --> 15:27.787
Good, right?

15:29.292 --> 15:31.308
Not bad, actually.

15:32.248 --> 15:34.787
I need to stay here a bit.

15:35.422 --> 15:38.030
- What?
- Just let me stay.

15:38.030 --> 15:39.683
Consider this whiskey your rent.

15:39.683 --> 15:41.117
Probably over 3 million won.

15:41.117 --> 15:43.659
Are you out of your mind right now?

15:43.659 --> 15:44.690
Leave.

15:44.690 --> 15:45.813
My place isn't some shelter.

15:45.813 --> 15:47.987
There's literally nowhere else for me.

15:47.987 --> 15:49.813
I ran into trouble and left my apartment,

15:49.813 --> 15:51.727
and finding a new place isn't realistic.

15:51.727 --> 15:54.248
My family, you know how it is...

15:54.248 --> 15:56.917
they've never done a thing for me.

15:57.595 --> 15:59.378
I hear you,

15:59.378 --> 16:02.873
but you can't just crash at a guy's place.
That's not okay.

16:04.943 --> 16:07.117
- Let me get you a hotel room.
- How many nights?

16:07.117 --> 16:09.205
There's no telling how long this drags out.

16:09.205 --> 16:11.265
Do you have 10 million to spare?

16:15.857 --> 16:18.248
Looks like that's a hard no.

16:18.248 --> 16:20.770
Alright, I'll leave.

16:20.770 --> 16:22.465
Maybe I'll sleep at some sauna,

16:22.465 --> 16:24.465
or just lie down on the sidewalk.

16:24.465 --> 16:27.292
If some random guy starts following me?
Oh well,

16:27.292 --> 16:30.508
I'll just go with him.
Not in a position to be choosy.

16:30.508 --> 16:32.395
Take care.

16:42.552 --> 16:44.292
This is temporary.

16:44.292 --> 16:46.657
The second it's sorted, you're out.

16:49.638 --> 16:51.205
The smaller room's mine.

16:51.205 --> 16:53.683
Keep the bigger one.

16:53.683 --> 16:55.395
Thanks.

16:56.595 --> 16:57.857
Hold on!

16:57.857 --> 17:00.135
Like that's not a given?

17:02.465 --> 17:05.048
Where does all this nerve come from?

17:10.457 --> 17:12.096
Could you take a look at the shower?

17:12.096 --> 17:14.515
It might be dripping again.

17:14.515 --> 17:16.570
Sure, I'll check it out.

17:17.857 --> 17:20.483
Never actually fixes anything...

17:22.457 --> 17:25.685
Did you see that parking lot post
on CompanyLife?

17:25.685 --> 17:26.695
[Seriously? It's a parking lot, not a bedroom!]

17:27.475 --> 17:30.048
I read it, yeah.

17:30.868 --> 17:33.055
Some people are unreal.

17:33.055 --> 17:36.917
We don't even do it in our own bedroom,
but they're doing it at the office?

17:53.726 --> 17:55.873
Should we try it?

17:59.900 --> 18:02.483
I'm beat.

18:06.117 --> 18:09.036
Hard pass for me too.

18:09.036 --> 18:10.465
Turn off the light.

18:10.465 --> 18:12.743
Do it yourself.

18:28.327 --> 18:29.777
Looks like you dropped some weight.

18:29.777 --> 18:32.111
Your face got even tinier.

18:32.111 --> 18:35.222
Is it stress? From Joo In Ah?

18:36.168 --> 18:37.864
Stick to that whiskey you brought over.

18:37.864 --> 18:40.483
Quit taking my beer.

18:40.483 --> 18:43.422
She really bothers you that much?

18:43.422 --> 18:44.684
How come?

18:44.684 --> 18:46.344
For making you the "cheating specialist"?

18:46.344 --> 18:49.063
Not cheating, it's PM.

18:49.063 --> 18:51.770
She hasn't figured out who I am yet.

18:51.770 --> 18:54.356
I had a case going in Team 1, right?

18:54.356 --> 18:58.281
Everything's filed in the handover folder,
and once she goes through it,

18:58.281 --> 19:00.465
she'll see what I bring to the table
and pull me back.

19:00.465 --> 19:02.787
Assuming she's any good.

19:03.635 --> 19:05.074
Come on,

19:05.074 --> 19:07.741
a guy like me shouldn't be stuck doing this.

19:07.741 --> 19:08.770
What's wrong?

19:08.770 --> 19:10.744
Sounds like it's right up your alley.

19:10.744 --> 19:12.383
PM, cheating, whatever you call it.

19:12.383 --> 19:14.903
How is that... what?

19:15.916 --> 19:16.953
Wait a second.

19:16.953 --> 19:20.570
Actually, you're ideal for it.

19:22.465 --> 19:24.857
Hey.

19:24.857 --> 19:28.053
That's word for word what Joo In Ah told me.

19:28.053 --> 19:29.084
How am I the perfect fit?

19:29.084 --> 19:31.283
Love affairs and drama.

19:31.283 --> 19:32.873
You're basically an expert.

19:32.873 --> 19:35.271
She barely knows anything about me.

19:35.271 --> 19:38.438
When has she ever caught me
in a situation like...

19:39.509 --> 19:41.352
Hang on...

19:41.352 --> 19:43.657
That silhouette...

19:46.900 --> 19:49.352
Did she see it?

19:50.857 --> 19:53.917
So that's the reason...

19:54.726 --> 19:56.873
she chose me?

19:58.726 --> 20:01.700
Can't be.

20:02.509 --> 20:04.395
Or could it?

20:05.335 --> 20:07.135
Is it possible?

20:08.117 --> 20:10.595
Straight black hair.

20:10.595 --> 20:12.527
White top.

20:18.900 --> 20:21.962
Is that some kind of uniform?

20:40.030 --> 20:42.335
Can't really say.

20:42.335 --> 20:44.743
Might not have been her.

20:51.261 --> 20:53.943
What's with the look?

20:53.943 --> 20:55.378
Something on my back or what?

20:55.378 --> 20:57.873
Just came for some coffee, that's all.

20:59.292 --> 21:02.105
Feels like there's something on your mind.

21:02.105 --> 21:03.117
Mr. Noh.

21:03.117 --> 21:07.027
If you're struggling with anything,
feel free to speak up.

21:07.027 --> 21:08.030
Okay.

21:08.030 --> 21:11.161
Better to just ask than sit here overthinking.

21:11.161 --> 21:12.162
Ms. Joo.

21:12.162 --> 21:14.005
Actually, hold on.

21:15.465 --> 21:18.787
There's no way I can ask
"Did you catch me kissing?"

21:19.639 --> 21:21.483
Tell me.

21:22.134 --> 21:23.857
About the parking garage, what's the plan?

21:23.857 --> 21:27.900
Our sources verified those rumors are real.

21:27.900 --> 21:30.497
Maybe post a "no inappropriate conduct" sign?

21:30.497 --> 21:32.248
That leaves us with zero results.

21:32.248 --> 21:33.557
Someone has to get caught.

21:33.557 --> 21:34.679
Catch people?

21:34.679 --> 21:36.552
And how exactly do we pull that off?

21:36.552 --> 21:38.422
It's not like I can
stake the place out and wait.

21:38.422 --> 21:39.796
A stakeout?

21:39.796 --> 21:41.162
A stakeout?

21:41.162 --> 21:43.730
That's absolutely ridiculous.

21:43.730 --> 21:45.117
The audit team isn't law enforcement.

21:45.117 --> 21:46.737
Surveillance for an audit, really?

21:46.737 --> 21:47.855
Exactly, right?

21:47.855 --> 21:48.856
That's what I'm saying.

21:48.856 --> 21:50.205
My point exactly.

21:50.205 --> 21:55.055
Though I heard years ago, one auditor
used a drone to snap photos.

21:55.055 --> 21:57.216
Seriously, what kind of auditor does that?

21:57.216 --> 21:59.830
It's not some hobby club. Right?

22:04.726 --> 22:07.295
Down your coffee and get moving.

22:07.295 --> 22:09.962
My clothes are stuck. My legs...

22:11.117 --> 22:15.639
Nothing else was available from the fleet.

22:15.639 --> 22:18.683
I should've brought my own car.

22:18.683 --> 22:22.639
If I slide this seat all the way back,
you'll have extra space in the front.

22:22.639 --> 22:24.595
- No, don't worry about it.
- One moment, just let me...

22:24.595 --> 22:26.830
- Just a second...
- Really, it's okay.

22:30.465 --> 22:32.700
I'm sorry.

22:47.987 --> 22:50.900
Seriously, what are we even doing?

22:50.900 --> 22:53.000
And you too.

22:53.000 --> 22:56.965
All that hard work in school wasn't for this.

22:56.965 --> 23:00.422
Good grades, a solid resume,
and it ends up here?

23:00.422 --> 23:03.987
My school wasn't anything like yours,

23:03.987 --> 23:06.813
and there's not much on my resume either.

23:06.813 --> 23:11.465
The Seohae plant's community hire program
brought me in. Pure luck.

23:11.465 --> 23:13.030
During the interview I told them,

23:13.030 --> 23:15.857
"White blood runs through my veins!"

23:15.857 --> 23:19.222
And they appreciated that old-fashioned energy.

23:20.769 --> 23:22.962
White blood!

23:24.354 --> 23:26.749
- The company mascot bird, right?
- Yeah.

23:26.749 --> 23:30.222
- That explains the White Blood Cell nickname.
- Bingo.

23:34.248 --> 23:36.900
A sharp guy like you probably feels like

23:36.900 --> 23:40.073
Team 3 assignments are too small,

23:40.073 --> 23:43.590
but being at Haemu Group,
this place everyone dreams about,

23:43.590 --> 23:46.552
and especially at HQ's audit office,
the best of the best,

23:46.552 --> 23:48.291
that alone means everything to me.

23:48.291 --> 23:51.308
Every day still feels like a blessing.

24:04.639 --> 24:06.161
Hey, White Blood Cell.

24:06.161 --> 24:08.002
Yes.

24:08.002 --> 24:10.552
My eyes were just shut
for an extended period. Not sleeping.

24:10.552 --> 24:12.204
Can you recall

24:12.204 --> 24:14.830
what Joo In Ah...

24:18.335 --> 24:21.683
had on her first day?

24:21.683 --> 24:23.557
Give me a second...

24:23.557 --> 24:25.623
My recall for stuff like this is incredible.

24:25.623 --> 24:27.662
Okay.

24:27.662 --> 24:29.700
Try to remember.

24:30.552 --> 24:32.726
What did she have on?

24:32.726 --> 24:35.145
So below the waist,

24:35.987 --> 24:38.222
dark pants.

24:39.656 --> 24:42.117
What about up top?

24:42.117 --> 24:44.536
Up there...

24:44.536 --> 24:47.117
black, too.

24:47.117 --> 24:49.030
- Positive?
- Absolutely.

24:49.030 --> 24:51.042
Oh, nice.

24:51.042 --> 24:53.004
Black.

24:55.255 --> 24:57.781
Hold on, though...

24:57.781 --> 25:00.596
could've been a white blouse.

25:00.596 --> 25:02.395
Seriously,

25:03.074 --> 25:05.005
a white one?

25:06.204 --> 25:07.601
Maybe not?

25:07.601 --> 25:08.639
What?

25:08.639 --> 25:10.509
Was it dark?

25:10.509 --> 25:11.987
The dark one?

25:11.987 --> 25:13.683
No, scratch that.

25:13.683 --> 25:15.150
It was white.

25:15.150 --> 25:17.552
Definitely white.

25:17.552 --> 25:19.657
Are you kidding me?

25:21.030 --> 25:23.509
I'm fairly certain it was white.

25:23.509 --> 25:25.639
Or maybe not?

25:25.639 --> 25:27.813
- Never mind.
- Yeah.

25:27.813 --> 25:29.726
I'm going to get coffee. Just wake up.

25:29.726 --> 25:31.962
Got it.

25:59.900 --> 26:02.309
Still can't shake this feeling.

26:05.241 --> 26:07.479
What am I even doing?

26:07.479 --> 26:09.162
Even if she saw it, then what?

26:09.162 --> 26:10.257
Whatever.

26:10.257 --> 26:11.813
It's not like I committed a crime.

26:11.813 --> 26:14.291
Forget it.

26:14.291 --> 26:16.135
Oh, you scared me!

26:17.770 --> 26:20.005
Why are you so jumpy?

26:22.552 --> 26:25.265
That was so sudden.

26:25.987 --> 26:28.378
Is a sudden entrance off-limits now?

26:28.378 --> 26:31.005
Do I need to knock before coming in?

26:32.900 --> 26:34.552
For what reason?

26:34.552 --> 26:36.438
Did I catch you...

26:37.649 --> 26:40.195
in the middle of something like this?

26:57.465 --> 26:59.438
Wait...

27:00.639 --> 27:01.857
she saw...

27:01.857 --> 27:04.743
She definitely saw it, right?

27:42.465 --> 27:44.438
Noh Ki Jun.

27:45.221 --> 27:46.885
What?

27:46.885 --> 27:48.502
You said no acknowledging
each other at the office.

27:48.502 --> 27:50.638
There's no one here.

27:50.638 --> 27:52.552
Joo In Ah giving you trouble again?

27:52.552 --> 27:53.813
You look terrible.

27:53.813 --> 27:55.284
Pretty much.

27:55.284 --> 27:58.111
Pick a warm spot
with good sunlight for my grave.

27:58.111 --> 28:00.191
Why accept it without a fight?

28:00.191 --> 28:01.987
There's a way out for you.

28:01.987 --> 28:03.987
I mean Executive Kim.

28:03.987 --> 28:06.205
The VP's dinner plans got canceled,

28:06.205 --> 28:08.917
so he's looking for a drinking buddy.

28:24.442 --> 28:26.362
Oh, hello sir.

28:26.362 --> 28:27.987
This is Noh Ki Jun, assistant manager.

28:27.987 --> 28:29.787
Yes.

28:36.271 --> 28:37.683
Joo In Ah

28:37.683 --> 28:41.248
never backs down, even with the higher-ups.

28:41.248 --> 28:44.216
You think the rest of us
don't have it in us to be that bold?

28:44.216 --> 28:46.236
That's just how corporate life works.

28:46.236 --> 28:47.611
Right, yeah.

28:47.611 --> 28:50.692
She does that with the higher-ups too?

28:50.692 --> 28:53.813
At least she doesn't just push
around the ones beneath her.

28:53.813 --> 28:59.653
Oh, whether she's tough
on the weak or whatever,

28:59.653 --> 29:03.611
and honestly,
how can someone have such bad judgment?

29:03.611 --> 29:09.032
I mean, our ace, you stuck in Team 3,

29:09.032 --> 29:10.291
doing PM work?

29:10.291 --> 29:12.117
I mean, PM work? Of all things?

29:12.117 --> 29:13.770
That's exactly it.

29:13.770 --> 29:16.117
It's been really rough, sir.

29:16.117 --> 29:19.853
Take it easy, alright?

29:19.853 --> 29:21.733
You know who I am, right?

29:21.733 --> 29:24.509
Now this is still

29:24.509 --> 29:27.527
between us, but...

29:32.509 --> 29:37.078
there's a new department I'm putting together.

29:37.078 --> 29:40.508
Kind of a command center

29:40.508 --> 29:44.726
for the whole group.

29:44.726 --> 29:47.117
Strategic Management...

29:47.117 --> 29:50.335
General Management Control Division.

29:50.335 --> 29:54.083
General Management Control Division.

29:54.083 --> 29:55.248
The name alone sounds huge.

29:55.248 --> 29:57.596
Huge, right?

29:57.596 --> 30:00.656
Your name's already been mentioned.

30:00.656 --> 30:04.613
You'll be free from there before long.

30:07.857 --> 30:09.485
Let me pour you one, sir.

30:09.485 --> 30:11.322
Okay.

30:13.074 --> 30:18.248
To our General Management...

30:18.248 --> 30:20.552
- Control Division.
- Control Division's

30:20.552 --> 30:22.857
bright future.

30:22.857 --> 30:24.873
Cheers!

30:33.161 --> 30:35.438
That hits the spot.

30:48.596 --> 30:49.771
I'll take off first.

30:49.771 --> 30:52.222
Alright, see you in the morning.

30:57.596 --> 30:59.050
It's raining.

30:59.050 --> 31:01.005
When are you getting off?

31:03.623 --> 31:05.127
I'm working late.

31:05.127 --> 31:07.395
Buy an umbrella and head home first.

31:25.476 --> 31:27.700
Hello?

31:30.552 --> 31:32.483
Jun Seo?

31:33.857 --> 31:36.305
That was so typical of us back then.

31:36.305 --> 31:40.605
We were so young and completely fearless.

31:40.605 --> 31:42.873
Reaching out was the right call.

31:49.900 --> 31:52.345
Is this really enough without actual food?

31:52.345 --> 31:54.905
You normally eat a ton.

31:54.905 --> 31:57.787
Whatever works. As long as I'm with you.

32:00.465 --> 32:03.178
Right, exactly.

32:06.936 --> 32:09.774
Look at all this rain.

32:17.509 --> 32:18.900
Let's...

32:18.900 --> 32:19.987
What?

32:19.987 --> 32:22.248
Stay together?

32:22.248 --> 32:24.483
Just till the rain stops.

32:53.693 --> 32:55.116
[Send]

32:56.162 --> 32:57.288
[Email sent successfully]

32:58.074 --> 32:59.917
Sent it.

33:00.987 --> 33:03.335
Great work today.

33:03.335 --> 33:04.422
You beat?

33:04.422 --> 33:05.459
Good work today.

33:05.459 --> 33:06.508
Not at all.

33:06.508 --> 33:08.370
Honestly, I feel amazing right now.

33:08.370 --> 33:10.890
It was my very first time working overtime.

33:10.890 --> 33:12.552
Yeah?

33:12.552 --> 33:15.451
How about we get a drink to celebrate?

33:15.451 --> 33:16.970
Absolutely!

33:16.970 --> 33:18.466
Let's go get something good.

33:18.466 --> 33:19.621
Sure. Wrap up and let's go.

33:19.621 --> 33:21.527
Sounds good.

33:29.205 --> 33:30.612
[Wife]

33:41.335 --> 33:43.613
I said go home without me.

33:46.117 --> 33:48.222
Are you soaked?

33:54.291 --> 33:56.483
This is wrong.

34:00.639 --> 34:03.178
The rain already stopped.

34:04.422 --> 34:05.960
Let's do it.

34:05.960 --> 34:08.901
- What?
- I said let's do it.

34:08.901 --> 34:11.165
We can't keep going like this.
We need to do this.

34:11.165 --> 34:13.352
What's gotten into you?

34:15.030 --> 34:16.406
Fine. Home first, all right?

34:16.406 --> 34:18.505
You're going to catch a cold.

34:18.505 --> 34:19.986
Let's do it here.

34:19.986 --> 34:23.032
This is the place, right? Section F.

34:32.335 --> 34:34.265
Come on.

34:39.770 --> 34:42.613
- What's wrong with you?
- Don't ruin the moment.

35:23.466 --> 35:25.162
Chairman gave the green light.

35:25.162 --> 35:27.963
You'll leave Audit any day now.

35:27.963 --> 35:31.438
Nice shot, sir!

35:34.074 --> 35:37.135
♪ I'm the best ♪

35:37.813 --> 35:40.813
♪ I'm the best ♪

35:40.813 --> 35:42.161
Think you'll finish up early?

35:42.161 --> 35:43.986
Let me see if I can cut out soon.
We'll eat well tonight.

35:43.986 --> 35:46.030
Sure. Don't take forever.

35:46.030 --> 35:47.867
Okay.

35:51.622 --> 35:53.037
Good morning.

35:53.037 --> 35:55.125
Good morning.

35:58.987 --> 36:01.438
Gorgeous day out, isn't it?

36:02.204 --> 36:05.642
That's a great look on you today.

36:05.642 --> 36:07.683
- Really?
- Yeah.

36:07.683 --> 36:10.639
You two look great together.

36:10.639 --> 36:13.178
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

36:24.752 --> 36:26.406
Good morning.

36:26.406 --> 36:28.205
Morning, Mr. Noh.

36:28.205 --> 36:29.726
You really love your button-downs, huh?

36:29.726 --> 36:31.787
Looks great on you.

36:32.638 --> 36:34.378
You seem cheerful.

36:34.378 --> 36:36.162
Did something good happen today?

36:36.162 --> 36:38.073
Why would I be in a bad mood?

36:38.073 --> 36:39.547
Beautiful day, life is...

36:39.547 --> 36:42.066
Actually, I've got one for you.

36:42.066 --> 36:45.186
Not one catch at the garage so far.

36:45.186 --> 36:47.596
You're not phoning this in again
like the Son case, are you?

36:47.596 --> 36:50.524
Just letting it slide?

36:50.524 --> 36:51.554
Do better.

36:51.554 --> 36:55.433
No assignment here is
less important than another.

36:55.433 --> 36:57.611
Sure. Just go with it.

36:57.611 --> 36:58.988
She's almost out of my life anyway.

36:58.988 --> 37:00.563
Absolutely.

37:00.563 --> 37:03.385
I drove my own car in for a real stakeout.

37:03.385 --> 37:06.185
Let you down again?

37:06.185 --> 37:08.308
No way.

37:15.639 --> 37:17.111
Ma'am.

37:17.111 --> 37:20.422
The shopping mall had this huge prize event,

37:20.422 --> 37:23.192
and the phones won't stop ringing.
"Is this legit?

37:23.192 --> 37:24.912
I put in so many entries,

37:24.912 --> 37:27.092
why didn't I win anything?"

37:27.092 --> 37:29.900
Since when is Audit a customer service hotline?

37:29.900 --> 37:33.032
Mr. Noh, stay on the parking garage case.

37:33.032 --> 37:34.672
Wait a second...

37:34.672 --> 37:37.631
You could really use backup for a stakeout,
right?

37:37.631 --> 37:40.511
One moment.

37:40.511 --> 37:44.005
Even Hyun Gyu's tied up on calls.
There's nobody left.

37:44.639 --> 37:46.963
Nobody available? How?

37:46.963 --> 37:49.657
Our finest asset is standing right here.

37:50.422 --> 37:52.222
Who?

37:59.622 --> 38:02.544
What's wrong with you? It's making me uneasy.

38:03.848 --> 38:04.857
Why not?

38:04.857 --> 38:08.395
Do you think it's not a job
for someone like you?

38:09.298 --> 38:13.763
Someone told me no Audit task
is beneath anyone.

38:17.932 --> 38:19.975
All right, then.

38:19.975 --> 38:23.731
Let's have ourselves a cozy, useful session.

38:30.736 --> 38:33.246
The seatbelt's a bit much, isn't it?

38:33.246 --> 38:35.395
We're not driving anywhere.

38:37.115 --> 38:38.248
My choice.

38:38.248 --> 38:40.465
You probably just spaced out.

38:40.465 --> 38:42.292
Take it off. Can't be comfortable like that.

38:42.292 --> 38:44.246
I'm totally fine right now.

38:44.246 --> 38:46.436
Couldn't be more relaxed. Super comfy.

38:46.436 --> 38:49.700
Seriously, just undo it.
Don't let pride get in the way.

38:50.683 --> 38:52.465
It happens.

38:52.465 --> 38:55.595
This kind of thing takes practice anyway.

38:55.595 --> 38:57.527
No worries.

38:59.116 --> 39:02.852
You sure know your way
around this type of case.

39:02.852 --> 39:05.030
I'm sorry?

39:05.030 --> 39:06.987
Naturally you'd be familiar.

39:06.987 --> 39:10.352
With situations like this.

39:12.726 --> 39:14.465
Ma'am,

39:14.465 --> 39:15.762
about that thing...

39:15.762 --> 39:16.800
Which thing?

39:16.800 --> 39:20.291
- What do you mean?
- The thing you saw.

39:20.291 --> 39:21.900
That whole scene,

39:21.900 --> 39:24.373
I'm not some creep or anything.

39:24.373 --> 39:25.421
The thing is...

39:25.421 --> 39:26.839
my lips just kind of...

40:11.030 --> 40:12.552
Let me handle this.

40:12.552 --> 40:14.527
It's my responsibility.

40:25.768 --> 40:28.982
Opening the car door. Audit team.

40:36.904 --> 40:39.492
Opening up.

40:46.248 --> 40:49.117
Oh my, Executive Kim.

40:49.117 --> 40:51.527
I heard you were so busy.

40:52.900 --> 40:55.292
- Wait.
- So what's this about, you two?

40:55.292 --> 40:57.726
Seriously?

40:57.726 --> 41:00.205
Folks like you should know better than this.

41:00.205 --> 41:04.048
Each of you has a family waiting, right?

41:06.267 --> 41:09.596
Just close that, will you?

41:09.596 --> 41:12.265
Sort it out and step outside.

41:19.822 --> 41:21.639
Classic Mr. Noh right there.

41:21.639 --> 41:24.028
You keep every promise you make.

41:24.028 --> 41:25.744
What a massive catch you pulled in.

41:25.744 --> 41:27.811
A real whopper!

41:27.811 --> 41:31.117
No wonder you're the best in Audit, huh?

41:31.117 --> 41:32.465
Wait a second.

41:32.465 --> 41:36.715
You reported straight to Executive Kim,
didn't you?

41:38.188 --> 41:40.248
Years of working together

41:40.248 --> 41:44.204
and you brought your own boss down
without blinking.

41:44.204 --> 41:45.987
Imagine how much better things would be

41:45.987 --> 41:49.117
if everyone followed your lead.

41:49.117 --> 41:50.805
Right?

41:57.185 --> 41:58.943
Excuse me.

41:58.943 --> 42:01.857
Could Executive Kim walk away clean

42:01.857 --> 42:04.552
- the same way Deputy Manager Son did?
- Not a chance.

42:04.552 --> 42:06.910
His case is nothing like Deputy Manager Son's.

42:06.910 --> 42:08.074
The man holds an executive title.

42:08.074 --> 42:09.596
One contract termination and he's out the door.

42:09.596 --> 42:11.925
They'd actually fire him?

42:11.925 --> 42:14.552
Still, the company can't really do
without Executive Kim...

42:14.552 --> 42:16.465
That man is far from indispensable.

42:16.465 --> 42:18.595
He does nothing, he's dead weight,

42:18.595 --> 42:20.825
and just because he's on the chairman's side,
he acts like a big shot.

42:20.825 --> 42:23.761
The vice chairman's been itching
to cut him loose.

42:23.761 --> 42:28.476
You gift-wrapped the perfect reason for him.

42:32.770 --> 42:34.962
So Executive Kim?

42:36.204 --> 42:38.483
It's over for him.

42:43.943 --> 42:48.335
[This area is for parking only]

42:48.335 --> 42:52.782
[No Parking]

43:05.943 --> 43:08.352
[Executive Kim Han Soo]

43:11.161 --> 43:15.135
Your call can't be completed.
Redirecting to voicemail...

43:25.864 --> 43:26.900
[Big Sister]

43:26.900 --> 43:27.915
[Pick Up]

43:28.857 --> 43:30.987
- That's so hilarious.
- Hey, sis.

43:30.987 --> 43:32.530
Ki Jun? Hello?

43:32.530 --> 43:34.669
When are you getting here?

43:34.669 --> 43:37.613
I'm on my way. Almost there.

43:41.248 --> 43:44.489
That bathroom handle needs fixing too.

43:44.489 --> 43:46.308
Sure.

43:47.030 --> 43:48.529
Hey, Noh Ki Jun.

43:48.529 --> 43:50.723
Check Jin Young's laptop, will you?

43:50.723 --> 43:51.749
The laptop?

43:51.749 --> 43:54.609
Ki Jun, something's off with that couch.
Take a look.

43:54.609 --> 43:55.990
There's only one of me, all right?

43:55.990 --> 43:58.265
One at a time.

43:59.343 --> 44:01.178
The couch?

44:02.162 --> 44:04.073
- Which side is wobbly?
- The left side.

44:04.073 --> 44:06.092
Look at my boy.

44:07.378 --> 44:12.657
Our precious youngest, always so helpful.

44:13.639 --> 44:16.787
Mom, come on, seriously.

44:21.857 --> 44:24.657
Mom, this meat is so good.

44:27.009 --> 44:29.067
Why are you drinking so much?

44:29.067 --> 44:30.967
Look at him. He barely touched his food.

44:30.967 --> 44:33.348
You can't even handle your liquor.

44:33.348 --> 44:34.756
Stop drinking!

44:34.756 --> 44:36.935
Stop pinching me, seriously.

44:36.935 --> 44:38.465
Just leave me alone.

44:38.465 --> 44:40.107
Is something wrong?

44:40.107 --> 44:42.086
Yeah, seriously. What's going on?

44:42.086 --> 44:44.659
Is somebody messing with you?

44:44.659 --> 44:45.987
What?

44:45.987 --> 44:47.687
Who is it? Which punk is it?

44:47.687 --> 44:49.641
Take them to court, okay?

44:49.641 --> 44:50.943
Get your brother-in-law on it...

44:50.943 --> 44:52.341
- We should talk it out first.
- Sue...

44:52.341 --> 44:53.378
I'll call them for you.

44:53.378 --> 44:55.943
Just stop it. Leave me alone.

44:55.943 --> 44:57.943
We need a name first. Who is it?

44:57.943 --> 44:59.121
We should talk it out first.

44:59.121 --> 45:01.857
Talk it out? Look at the state he's in.

45:01.857 --> 45:04.248
Just call your husband already.

45:04.248 --> 45:08.008
What kind of scumbag
would do this to our precious boy?

45:08.008 --> 45:09.111
Gosh.

45:09.111 --> 45:12.117
- Who is it? Tell us.
- I'm saying we need to talk it out!

45:12.117 --> 45:14.348
We need a name. What's the name?

45:14.348 --> 45:17.520
- Tell us.
- Just say the name.

45:19.683 --> 45:21.205
No, just stop it!

45:21.205 --> 45:22.335
Who is it?

45:22.335 --> 45:23.987
Just tell us!

45:23.987 --> 45:25.901
I just... I hate you guys!

45:25.901 --> 45:28.070
Leave me alone!

45:28.070 --> 45:29.204
No.

45:29.204 --> 45:30.904
Make the call!

45:30.904 --> 45:33.095
Call them! Call customer service!

45:33.095 --> 45:36.873
- What customer service?
- Call customer service!

45:45.117 --> 45:47.545
[Haemu Pharma]

45:50.770 --> 45:53.465
[Noh Ki Jun Audit Team 1 Handover]

45:53.465 --> 45:54.843
[Haemu Pharma 2025 Contract Audit]

45:58.162 --> 45:59.900
[Noh Ki Jun Audit Team 1 Handover]

45:59.900 --> 46:03.943
[Delete Noh Ki Jun Audit Team 1 Handover
and all subfolders for good?]

46:03.943 --> 46:04.945
[Confirm]

46:24.336 --> 46:26.986
Executive Kim's situation is regrettable.

46:26.986 --> 46:28.296
Did you burn him intentionally?

46:28.296 --> 46:30.048
No.

46:30.048 --> 46:31.650
It came up by accident
while auditing something else.

46:31.650 --> 46:32.926
What a letdown.

46:32.926 --> 46:34.770
I figured you'd picked up some edge,

46:34.770 --> 46:37.175
but it was all just dumb luck.

46:37.175 --> 46:39.683
I haven't given you anything yet.

46:39.683 --> 46:41.422
Prove yourself.

46:41.422 --> 46:43.787
Prove you're not like your mother.

47:06.410 --> 47:10.074
Honey, Seong Yeol is here.

47:10.074 --> 47:11.422
Say hi to your father.

47:11.422 --> 47:13.527
I'll go make some coffee.

47:15.117 --> 47:18.005
Father, your youngest is here.

47:18.670 --> 47:20.531
Oh, you're here too?

47:20.531 --> 47:22.395
It's been a while.

47:23.770 --> 47:25.630
Father, how's your health?

47:25.630 --> 47:28.161
You're supposed to be lying low,
and no one sent for you.

47:28.161 --> 47:29.987
How dare you show your face here?

47:29.987 --> 47:32.700
Nice to know you're still the same as ever.

47:34.237 --> 47:36.823
How come neither of you two
has any middle ground?

47:36.823 --> 47:39.552
One of you is too soft to get anything done.

47:39.552 --> 47:43.335
And the other one's got no fear
and keeps causing trouble left and right.

47:43.335 --> 47:45.308
Good grief.

47:45.987 --> 47:49.248
So Dad, I went ahead...

47:49.248 --> 47:51.700
and caused another incident.

47:52.291 --> 47:56.292
That Saudi gas plant Package 1
you said you dreamed about...

47:56.292 --> 47:58.220
Plus Package 3 on top of that.

47:58.220 --> 48:01.813
A total of 8.77 billion dollars.

48:01.813 --> 48:04.048
I landed it.

48:10.046 --> 48:11.048
So, what do you think?

48:11.048 --> 48:14.487
Think I've earned my way back yet?

48:14.487 --> 48:17.527
I hear there's an open spot at HQ, too.

48:32.770 --> 48:34.547
Should I cancel lunch?

48:34.547 --> 48:37.205
You don't look like you're feeling great.

48:37.205 --> 48:39.135
I'm fine.

48:40.851 --> 48:43.378
Get me the staff evaluations

48:43.378 --> 48:45.809
and a shortlist of who's up for promotion.

48:45.809 --> 48:47.440
One more thing...

48:47.440 --> 48:50.780
Schedule a meal with QS International's
President Lee Hyung Geun,

48:50.780 --> 48:52.260
as soon as you can.

48:52.260 --> 48:54.720
Got it.

48:54.720 --> 48:56.069
Do you want to leave now?

48:56.069 --> 48:58.291
To the AI camp.

48:58.291 --> 49:00.308
Let's head out in 30.

49:01.683 --> 49:03.613
One moment, please.

49:24.770 --> 49:27.265
I can handle this myself.

49:27.900 --> 49:30.265
Just email me the files.

49:32.683 --> 49:34.527
Got it.

50:11.638 --> 50:13.117
Like what?

50:13.117 --> 50:15.527
No, you know what, what was it?

50:16.983 --> 50:19.781
Man, I need some sugar.

50:24.533 --> 50:28.498
Where did Ms. Yoon keep her jar?

50:29.117 --> 50:32.275
Found it. Ms. Yoon's candy jar.

50:32.275 --> 50:34.422
Got some weight to it.

50:34.422 --> 50:36.222
You got something new in here?

50:36.857 --> 50:39.483
This one's new to me.

50:41.476 --> 50:42.509
What is it?

50:42.509 --> 50:44.857
It's good.

50:44.857 --> 50:46.205
Like a mango thing?

50:46.205 --> 50:47.552
Oh right, Hae Young.

50:47.552 --> 50:48.770
What place did we pick for tonight?

50:48.770 --> 50:50.292
Kkul-kkul-i's Charcoal Pork BBQ.

50:50.292 --> 50:51.813
Pork again?

50:51.813 --> 50:54.508
It's Ms. Joo's welcome dinner.
Can't we step it up?

50:54.508 --> 50:57.117
The company dinner fund's almost tapped out.

50:57.117 --> 50:59.030
What's with you

50:59.030 --> 51:01.292
being so tight with the money?

51:01.292 --> 51:05.117
Did you take a special exam
on holding the vault key so tight?

51:05.117 --> 51:07.638
I've got no choice when a servant keeps

51:07.638 --> 51:09.030
draining the budget dry.

51:09.030 --> 51:10.314
A servant?

51:10.314 --> 51:11.352
Did you catch that?

51:11.352 --> 51:13.540
- You're calling me a servant right now?
- Hit a nerve?

51:13.540 --> 51:16.813
- Aren't we all just servants?
- What's wrong with you?

51:16.813 --> 51:20.117
Anyway, where did Mr. Noh go?
He's been gone for a while now.

51:20.117 --> 51:22.638
Mr. Noh's been a little off today...

51:22.638 --> 51:24.030
His face looked pretty rough.

51:24.030 --> 51:25.869
Just sighing left and right.

51:25.869 --> 51:29.117
Looked like he was tearing up a bit.

51:29.117 --> 51:32.638
- Anyway, he just seemed really sad.
- Really?

51:32.638 --> 51:33.943
Did he get dumped?

51:33.943 --> 51:35.508
Looks like it.

51:35.508 --> 51:37.954
Oh man, that's rough.

51:41.508 --> 51:43.962
Thanks for the candy.

52:03.048 --> 52:04.813
There...

52:04.813 --> 52:06.743
he goes.

52:11.514 --> 52:13.934
My only hope.

52:13.934 --> 52:16.314
My lifeline.

52:18.291 --> 52:20.483
Adios.

52:32.162 --> 52:33.727
Total prime real estate.

52:33.727 --> 52:34.770
Back then,

52:34.770 --> 52:36.770
it was all salt fields right outside the plant.

52:36.770 --> 52:38.533
All hell broke loose.

52:38.533 --> 52:40.835
You know what matters most for salt farming?

52:40.835 --> 52:42.652
It's the sun and the wind.

52:42.652 --> 52:45.153
But once you cover up the southeast,

52:45.153 --> 52:46.853
there's shade and the wind can't blow through.

52:46.853 --> 52:49.552
The salt won't crystallize at all.

52:49.552 --> 52:52.813
Right then, the guy who saved the day was...

52:52.813 --> 52:54.422
Mr. Baek.

52:54.422 --> 52:55.683
You should eat some too.

52:55.683 --> 52:57.633
I'm eating. I'm fine.

52:57.633 --> 53:00.952
You're making me look bad here.

53:00.952 --> 53:03.451
I'm the youngest one here.

53:03.451 --> 53:04.915
Seriously, don't worry about it.

53:04.915 --> 53:08.575
Because I just think that's how you are.

53:08.575 --> 53:10.161
That I'm just rude by nature?

53:10.161 --> 53:11.553
See, that land used to belong to...

53:11.553 --> 53:12.639
No, that's not what I meant.

53:12.639 --> 53:13.944
It was the perfect location...

53:13.944 --> 53:16.161
It's burning! Quick, eat up.

53:16.161 --> 53:18.900
- I'm telling you, Mr. Woo is something else.
- You're good at being passive-aggressive.

53:18.900 --> 53:20.378
[Watchlist]
Back when he first started in China,

53:20.378 --> 53:22.162
this one time...

53:22.162 --> 53:23.813
Really?

53:23.813 --> 53:24.915
What do you mean, really?

53:24.915 --> 53:26.435
- I haven't even said anything yet.
- What gives?

53:26.435 --> 53:27.857
It's not "what gives,"

53:27.857 --> 53:29.204
just hear me out.

53:29.204 --> 53:31.308
So this guy...

53:32.726 --> 53:35.011
Alright, Audit Team 3.
Let's have a drink together.

53:35.011 --> 53:37.475
Oh, you're here.

53:37.475 --> 53:39.727
Thanks.

53:39.727 --> 53:41.710
Alright, shall we all have a drink?

53:41.710 --> 53:43.570
Oh, hold on one second.

53:45.422 --> 53:47.205
- Yes, eat up everyone.
- Sure.

53:47.205 --> 53:48.811
At the end of the day,
we all work to eat, right?

53:48.811 --> 53:50.850
- Yes, thank you.
- Sure.

53:50.850 --> 53:52.515
Here, let me pour you one.

53:52.515 --> 53:54.552
- Sure thing.
- Enjoy your drinks.

53:54.552 --> 53:56.438
Thank you.

53:59.248 --> 54:02.135
Mr. Noh, let me pour you one too.

54:08.110 --> 54:09.683
Oh, soju.

54:09.683 --> 54:12.248
Okay.

54:12.248 --> 54:15.787
You really worked hard.

54:17.247 --> 54:18.335
You all know, right?

54:18.335 --> 54:19.811
He scored a big one.

54:19.811 --> 54:20.852
Of course.

54:20.852 --> 54:23.683
He's our team's pride and joy.

54:23.683 --> 54:26.161
Pride and joy, he says.

54:26.161 --> 54:30.509
Let's raise a glass to our Audit Team 3 ace.

54:30.509 --> 54:32.509
Alright.

54:32.509 --> 54:34.324
Here's to Mr. Noh!

54:34.324 --> 54:37.509
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

54:37.509 --> 54:39.352
Mr. Noh!

54:41.268 --> 54:43.222
So good.

54:45.022 --> 54:48.004
This drink hits different!

54:48.004 --> 54:49.921
Let me...

54:49.921 --> 54:50.965
Here's a wrap for you.

54:50.965 --> 54:54.374
♪ I need you, baby, bye bye bye ♪

54:54.374 --> 54:58.142
♪ Do you really have to go, why why why ♪

54:58.142 --> 55:00.857
♪ All those words are a lie lie lie ♪

55:00.857 --> 55:07.900
♪ I'll wait for you till the day I die ♪

55:07.900 --> 55:14.613
♪ Don't cry alone just because I'm not there ♪

55:20.596 --> 55:27.731
♪ Come back to me, my love ♪

55:27.731 --> 55:32.029
[Cancel]
♪ Don't you know ♪

55:32.029 --> 55:33.509
The vibe totally tanked.

55:33.509 --> 55:35.639
Tell me about it.

55:35.639 --> 55:37.248
Time for some CPR on this vibe.

55:37.248 --> 55:40.048
That's my job, right?

55:44.018 --> 55:46.813
Come on over and take a seat.

55:46.813 --> 55:49.092
TWIT!

55:59.248 --> 56:01.943
♪ You're a fool ♪

56:01.943 --> 56:03.987
♪ Twit twit twit twit ♪
♪ Twit twit twit twit ♪

56:03.987 --> 56:06.291
♪ I don't like it nobody likes it ♪

56:06.291 --> 56:08.987
♪ Fragile little Simcheong ♪

56:08.987 --> 56:10.943
♪ Twit twit twit twit ♪
♪ Twit twit twit twit ♪

56:10.943 --> 56:14.030
♪ I don't like it nobody likes it ♪

56:14.030 --> 56:16.657
♪ You're a fool ♪

56:20.291 --> 56:21.848
♪ Fragile little Simcheong ♪

56:21.848 --> 56:25.683
♪ Look around you once in a while ♪

56:25.683 --> 56:28.900
♪ You're hurting but you don't even know it ♪

56:28.900 --> 56:31.365
♪ You make me royal
You make me a hero ♪

56:31.365 --> 56:32.508
♪ You make me genius, yes ♪

56:32.508 --> 56:35.943
♪ You give so much, so why are you
the only one ending up miserable ♪

56:35.943 --> 56:39.074
♪ Because you only breathe for me ♪

56:39.074 --> 56:41.646
♪ You look so lonely ♪

56:41.646 --> 56:44.287
♪ You're a fool ♪

56:44.287 --> 56:46.291
♪ Twit twit twit twit ♪
♪ Twit twit twit twit ♪

56:46.291 --> 56:47.715
♪ I don't like it ♪

56:47.715 --> 56:50.085
[Cancel]
♪ Nobody likes it ♪

56:55.030 --> 56:57.422
Ma'am.

56:57.422 --> 57:00.352
Isn't this a bit much?

57:06.392 --> 57:08.311
Yes,

57:08.311 --> 57:11.335
I kissed someone!

57:11.335 --> 57:15.422
I know that's why you put me on PM duty.

57:15.422 --> 57:17.900
But so what?

57:17.900 --> 57:22.900
How is that a PM violation?

57:22.900 --> 57:25.528
Is there anyone here who doesn't kiss?

57:26.726 --> 57:29.338
You've never kissed anyone?

57:29.338 --> 57:32.265
I'm asking if you've never kissed!

58:24.422 --> 58:25.867
You alright?

58:25.867 --> 58:28.048
You were puking the whole night.

58:29.465 --> 58:31.352
Word is you went viral yesterday.

58:31.352 --> 58:32.734
Wait, how did you hear about that?

58:32.734 --> 58:34.194
Walls have ears in this company.

58:34.194 --> 58:37.857
A story that juicy travels fast.

58:37.857 --> 58:40.253
You've never been hated before, huh?

58:40.253 --> 58:43.433
You're everybody's golden boy.

58:43.433 --> 58:45.613
Golden boy, my ass.

58:50.378 --> 58:52.943
Come on, it's still a workplace.

58:52.943 --> 58:55.673
If I do good work,
they'll forget eventually, right?

58:55.673 --> 58:57.127
Ki Jun.

58:57.127 --> 59:00.248
When people like you, they just do.

59:00.248 --> 59:04.205
Once they hate you, nothing you do will fix it.

59:04.205 --> 59:09.683
Right now, she can't stand you no matter what.

59:09.683 --> 59:11.308
Maybe I should just walk out.

59:11.308 --> 59:13.747
At least go to work.

59:13.747 --> 59:16.189
You still have to turn in
your resignation in person.

59:16.189 --> 59:18.248
I'm taking the day off.

59:18.248 --> 59:20.178
Must be nice.

59:39.128 --> 59:41.726
Ma'am.

59:41.726 --> 59:43.291
I'm sorry about yesterday.

59:43.291 --> 59:45.563
You must be pretty disappointed.

59:45.563 --> 59:47.352
Excuse me?

59:49.465 --> 59:53.048
About not getting
into the General Management Control Division.

59:55.248 --> 59:58.477
If you wanted out of Audit that bad,
you should have just said so.

59:58.477 --> 01:00:00.903
I'm not that unreasonable.

01:00:00.903 --> 01:00:03.613
Don't go scheming behind my back.

01:00:04.529 --> 01:00:07.383
Oh, and just so you know,
that division got scrapped.

01:00:07.383 --> 01:00:09.787
When Executive Kim got the boot.

01:00:18.726 --> 01:00:21.917
How are you holding up?

01:00:22.596 --> 01:00:25.314
I think you're kind of cool, honestly.

01:00:25.314 --> 01:00:28.378
If that were me, no way I'd show my face.

01:00:28.378 --> 01:00:31.422
Why are you fanning the flames?

01:00:31.422 --> 01:00:34.248
Think about how hard this is for him right now.

01:00:34.248 --> 01:00:36.222
Right?

01:00:37.857 --> 01:00:40.917
He's the type to blow up out of nowhere.

01:00:48.987 --> 01:00:50.322
No, okay?

01:00:50.322 --> 01:00:52.135
It's not.

01:01:01.252 --> 01:01:03.162
[The name we built,
Haemu Recognized by the world first]

01:01:03.162 --> 01:01:04.296
[Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun, Audit Team 3]

01:01:05.162 --> 01:01:07.595
[Check Retirement Benefits]

01:01:07.595 --> 01:01:09.509
[Retirement Benefits: 40,788,560 won]

01:01:09.509 --> 01:01:10.987
Alright.

01:01:10.987 --> 01:01:13.596
I'll take a breather.

01:01:13.596 --> 01:01:16.005
I'll find another job.

01:01:16.857 --> 01:01:18.830
I'll just throw in the towel.

01:01:19.857 --> 01:01:21.022
[Resignation Letter]

01:01:22.683 --> 01:01:25.108
[Name: Noh Ki Jun]

01:01:38.414 --> 01:01:39.502
[Resignation Letter]

01:01:57.248 --> 01:01:59.873
There's something I need to say.

01:02:01.335 --> 01:02:02.862
Mr. Noh.

01:02:02.862 --> 01:02:04.743
Mr. Noh.

01:02:07.248 --> 01:02:09.787
Did you take what I printed out?

01:02:10.422 --> 01:02:11.913
[Audit Office Q3 Stationery Expenses]

01:02:15.409 --> 01:02:17.457
One second.

01:02:21.509 --> 01:02:23.308
Here.

01:02:45.813 --> 01:02:47.819
[New email:
"A tip about Head of Audit Joo In Ah"]

01:02:52.770 --> 01:02:54.967
[New email:
"A tip about Head of Audit Joo In Ah"]

01:03:04.552 --> 01:03:07.162
[Head of Audit]

01:03:07.162 --> 01:03:09.631
[Joo In Ah]

01:03:14.857 --> 01:03:19.030
[A tip about Head of Audit Joo In Ah]

01:03:19.030 --> 01:03:25.017
[Joo In Ah is in an inappropriate relationship
with a coworker]

01:04:24.248 --> 01:04:26.298
Scared you, right?

01:04:26.298 --> 01:04:29.273
If there's even a slim chance
that report is real,

01:04:29.273 --> 01:04:32.479
I'd have the ammo to finish Joo In Ah for good.

01:04:32.479 --> 01:04:33.594
- What?
- You scared me.

01:04:33.594 --> 01:04:34.730
He's a cougar magnet?

01:04:34.730 --> 01:04:36.161
I told you, stop doing this.

01:04:36.161 --> 01:04:38.596
Leave. Now.

01:04:38.596 --> 01:04:40.690
I can't believe she's cheating.

01:04:40.690 --> 01:04:43.641
Ever seen her come in with a man?

01:04:43.641 --> 01:04:45.410
Ten condoms? Really?

01:04:45.410 --> 01:04:49.117
There's one hell of a storm coming our way.

01:04:49.117 --> 01:04:52.743
What kind of person is Joo In Ah, anyway?
